Using MIT licensed icons in a website
text:
Hi, I want to use SVG icons (heroicons) licensed under MIT in a website

The license states - "The above copyright notice and this permission notice shall be included in all copies or substantial portions of the Software.".

Where do I need to put a copy of MIT license text? Do I put it as a comment in the SVG code of the icon? or make a separate "/license" page and say "Icons provided by heroicons licensed under MIT, license notice below - and then paste the MIT license text" is that fine?
